  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        patients with signs of severe GI-bleeding (with melena or dark bloody stool) and
        hemodynamic instability (defined as (pre)collapse or MAP &lt; 80 mmHg or HR &gt; 110) and/or drop
        of hemoglobin &gt; 2g/dl/d and/or need of transfusion of minimum of 2 packed red cells

        Exclusion Criteria:

        missing consent form, pregnancy, origin of bleeding found in upper GI-endoscopy (e.g. blood
        in the stomach, ulcer, varices with signs of bleeding, mallory-weiss-tear, Angiodysplasia
        (with signs of bleeding), refluxesophagitis LA C or D) fresh bloody stool, known stenosis
        of the bowel, known site of bleeding, known inflammatory bowel disease
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>18 Years</minimum_age>
